      "body" : "Great overview, thanks!\r\n\r\nRegarding `boost::filesystem`, this means that if we require at least 1.44 we can rid of some compatibility logic here:\r\n```\r\nsrc/qt/guiutil.cpp:#if BOOST_FILESYSTEM_VERSION >= 3\r\nsrc/qt/guiutil.cpp:#if BOOST_FILESYSTEM_VERSION >= 3\r\nsrc/qt/guiutil.cpp:#if BOOST_FILESYSTEM_VERSION >= 3\r\nsrc/test/testutil.cpp:#if BOOST_FILESYSTEM_VERSION == 3\r\n```\r\nMost notably the GUI thing: \"Conversion between boost path and QString can use invalid character encoding with boost_filesystem v2 and older\"\r\n\r\nC++11 compliance is a good point and means we *need* to require a recent boost.\r\n\r\nDate information would also be useful here:\r\n```\r\nVersion 1.62.0  September 28th, 2016 15:17 GMT\r\nVersion 1.61.0  May 13th, 2016 02:58 GMT\r\nVersion 1.60.0  December 17th, 2015 15:52 GMT\r\nVersion 1.59.0  August 13th, 2015 15:23 GMT\r\nVersion 1.58.0  April 17th, 2015 07:53 GMT\r\nVersion 1.57.0  November 3rd, 2014 21:55 GMT\r\nVersion 1.56.0  August 7th, 2014 16:08 GMT\r\nVersion 1.55.0  November 11th, 2013 19:50 GMT\r\nVersion 1.54.0  July 1st, 2013 17:10 GMT\r\nVersion 1.53.0  February 4th, 2013 18:29 GMT\r\nVersion 1.52.0  November 5th, 2012 16:05 GMT\r\nVersion 1.51.0  August 20th, 2012 23:00 GMT\r\nVersion 1.50.0  June 28th, 2012 12:48 GMT\r\nVersion 1.49.0  February 24th, 2012 21:20 GMT\r\nVersion 1.48.0  November 15th, 2011 15:47 GMT\r\nVersion 1.47.0  July 11th, 2011 22:19 GMT\r\nVersion 1.46.1  March 12th, 2011 15:45 GMT\r\nVersion 1.46.0  February 21st, 2011 20:36 GMT\r\nVersion 1.45.0  November 19th, 2010 16:00 GMT\r\nVersion 1.44.0  August 13th, 2010 17:00 GMT\r\nVersion 1.43.0  May 6th, 2010 12:00 GMT\r\nVersion 1.42.0  February 2nd, 2010 14:00 GMT\r\nVersion 1.41.0  November 17th, 2009 17:00 GMT\r\nVersion 1.40.0  August 27th, 2009 17:00 GMT\r\nVersion 1.39.0  May 2nd, 2009 12:00 GMT\r\nVersion 1.38.0  February 8th, 2009 12:00 GMT\r\nVersion 1.37.0  November 3rd, 2008 12:00 GMT\r\nVersion 1.36.0  August 14t