      "body" : "Three possible scenarios:\r\n\r\n#### Bump to 1.44.0 (released August 2010)\r\n\r\nRequire Filesystem V3\r\n- Remove compatibility logic in [testutil.cpp](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/test/testutil.cpp)\r\n- Remove compatibility logic in guiutil.cpp [here](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/qt/guiutil.cpp#L40), [here](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/qt/guiutil.cpp#L69) and [here](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/qt/guiutil.cpp#L867). As well as a warning [here](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/qt/guiutil.cpp#L878).\r\n\r\nDownside: No C++11 compliance in Chrono or Thread \r\n- However Thread may be gone shortly anyways (see #8631), and would require a bump to 1.54.0, which is probably too recent a version.\r\n\r\n#### Bump to 1.52.0 (released November 2012)\r\n\r\nRequire Filesystem V3 + remove logic as above.\r\nC++11 compliance in Chrono\r\nNo C++11 compliance in Thread.\r\n- Remove checks for Boost < 1.49 & reduced exports in [configure](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/configure.ac#L616).\r\n- Possibly remove configure checks for broken Boost sleep in Boost < 1.52 ? [here](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/configure.ac#L699).\r\n- Remove Boost < 1.50 compatibility logic in [scheduler.cpp](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/scheduler.cpp#L48).\r\n- Issue with Boost < 1.46.0 on 32-bit systems in [coins.h](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/coins.h#L259)\r\n- Clang workaround for Boost < 1.46 in [util.cpp](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/src/util.cpp#L88)\r\n\r\n#### Bump to 1.54.0 (released July 2013)\r\n\r\nAll of the above \r\nC++11 compliance in Thread\r\n\r\nI had a feeling there was some Boost 1.36.0 logic somewhere, but I can't seem to find it now.\r\n",
